## Usage Rules

### Always Use shadcn/ui Components
✅ **CORRECT**:
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card";

export function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Button>Click me</Button>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

❌ **WRONG** - Never use raw HTML elements:
```tsx
export function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div className="card">
      <h2>Title</h2>
      <button>Click me</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Import Path
Always import components from `@/components/ui/`:
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
```

### Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling: `className="flex items-center gap-2"`
- Use component variants: `<Button variant="outline" size="sm">`
- Never write custom CSS for components

## Before Creating UI
**Always check if the component is installed first**. If you need a component that doesn't exist, run the appropriate `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]` command.
